Given a sorted array containing only 0s and 1s, find the transition point. 




Example 1:

Input:
N = 5
arr[] = {0,0,0,1,1}
Output: 3
Explanation: index 3 is the transition 
point where 1 begins.






class GfG {
    int transitionPoint(int arr[], int n) {
        // code here
        for(int i =0; i< n ; i++){
            if(arr[i] == 1 ){
                return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;    
    }
}
